1466
01:58:19,795 --> 01:58:22,036
Hello. Welcome.

1467
01:58:22,164 --> 01:58:24,735
Can we help you and
invite you to sit down?

1468
01:58:24,866 --> 01:58:27,074
You look like
you've traveled here.

1469
01:58:27,201 --> 01:58:30,547
- How else do you get someplace?
<font color="#D900D9">(NERVOUS CHUCKLE)</font>

1470
01:58:30,672 --> 01:58:34,380
- Can I assist you in help?
- I'm here to see Master.

1471
01:58:34,509 --> 01:58:37,978
- And what's your name?
- Freddie Quell.

1472
01:58:38,112 --> 01:58:41,356
- Is he expecting you?
- He should be.

1473
01:58:46,321 --> 01:58:48,232
I took that picture.

1474
01:59:10,978 --> 01:59:12,583
Hello, Freddie.

1475
01:59:13,749 --> 01:59:15,318
Val.

1476
01:59:16,418 --> 01:59:18,192
You look good.

1477
01:59:20,254 --> 01:59:21,893
<font color="#808080">VAL:</font> Come on.

1478
01:59:27,396 --> 01:59:30,343
- Can I get this for you?
- No, thank you.

1479
01:59:35,937 --> 01:59:39,442
- How are you?
- Couldn't be better.

1480
01:59:39,574 --> 01:59:41,781
<font color="#D900D9">(INDISTINCT CHATTER)</font>

1481
02:00:16,644 --> 02:00:18,124
Hello.

1482
02:00:18,813 --> 02:00:20,224
Hi.

1483
02:00:29,590 --> 02:00:32,231
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font> Thank you.

1484
02:00:33,462 --> 02:00:34,769
Thank you.

1485
02:00:52,047 --> 02:00:53,048
<font color="#D900D9">(INDISTINCT)</font>

1486
02:01:11,199 --> 02:01:12,973
Some place.

1487
02:01:19,141 --> 02:01:20,813
Are you drunk?

1488
02:01:22,611 --> 02:01:24,557
No. No, no.

1489
02:01:29,116 --> 02:01:31,562
You look sick.

1490
02:01:31,686 --> 02:01:33,687
Freddie, you don't look healthy.

1491
02:01:35,690 --> 02:01:38,830
I don't look like that.
That's not how I look.

1492
02:01:38,960 --> 02:01:41,496
<font color="#808080">PEGGY:</font>
You don't think you can?

1493
02:01:41,629 --> 02:01:43,438
It's just not how I look.

1494
02:01:46,500 --> 02:01:49,539
You can't take this life straight,
can you?

1495
02:01:56,644 --> 02:01:58,147
What do you want?

1496
02:02:01,316 --> 02:02:02,920
I don't know.

1497
02:02:05,353 --> 02:02:08,391
I had a dream...

1498
02:02:15,097 --> 02:02:17,008
Where's Elizabeth?

1499
02:02:19,067 --> 02:02:24,175
- DCF.
- Really? What is that?

1500
02:02:25,740 --> 02:02:29,449
What did you expect
would happen coming here?

1501
02:02:34,583 --> 02:02:36,790
I can take pictures...

1502
02:02:38,120 --> 02:02:39,929
...if you need them.

1503
02:02:41,857 --> 02:02:44,098
<font color="#808080">PEGGY:</font>
We don't need pictures, Freddie.

1504
02:02:46,962 --> 02:02:50,340
This is something you do
for a billion years or not at all.

1505
02:02:50,464 --> 02:02:52,808
This isn't fashion.

1506
02:03:01,876 --> 02:03:03,413
This is pointless.

1507
02:03:05,080 --> 02:03:07,458
He isn't interested
in getting better.

1508
02:03:17,791 --> 02:03:21,797
<font color="#D900D9">(DOOR OPENS, CLOSES)</font>

1509
02:03:21,929 --> 02:03:23,603
She's really softened up.

1510
02:03:34,175 --> 02:03:36,781
Free winds
and no tyranny for you?

1511
02:03:39,748 --> 02:03:41,192
Freddie...

1512
02:03:43,985 --> 02:03:48,695
...sailor of the seas.
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>

1513
02:03:48,822 --> 02:03:50,530
You pay no rent.

1514
02:03:52,160 --> 02:03:54,333
Free to go where you please.

1515
02:03:59,668 --> 02:04:01,807
Then go.

1516
02:04:03,871 --> 02:04:09,321
Go to that landless latitude,
and good luck.

1517
02:04:12,714 --> 02:04:17,663
For if you figure a way to live
without serving a master...

1518
02:04:19,654 --> 02:04:21,223
...any master...

1519
02:04:22,958 --> 02:04:25,962
...then let the rest us know,
will you?

1520
02:04:28,330 --> 02:04:31,799
For you'd be the first person
in the history of the world.

1521
02:04:37,205 --> 02:04:43,178
In my dream, you said you'd...
you figured out where we met.

1522
02:04:46,915 --> 02:04:52,023
I went back and I found it.

1523
02:04:52,152 --> 02:04:54,759
I recalled you and I working together...

1524
02:04:56,223 --> 02:04:58,965
...in Paris.

1525
02:04:59,094 --> 02:05:02,132
We were members
of the Pigeon Post.

1526
02:05:02,263 --> 02:05:04,607
During a four and a half month siege

1527
02:05:04,732 --> 02:05:07,269
of the city by Prussian forces.

1528
02:05:08,937 --> 02:05:12,474
We worked and rigged balloons...

1529
02:05:12,607 --> 02:05:16,487
...that delivered mail
and secret messages...

1530
02:05:16,611 --> 02:05:20,218
...across the communications blockade,

1531
02:05:20,348 --> 02:05:23,089
set up by the Prussians.

1532
02:05:23,218 --> 02:05:28,065
We sent 65 unguided mail balloons
and only two went missing.

1533
02:05:30,692 --> 02:05:32,797
In the worst winter on record.

1534
02:05:42,304 --> 02:05:43,749
Two.

1535
02:05:52,647 --> 02:05:56,026
If you leave here,
I don't ever want to see you again.

1536
02:06:05,559 --> 02:06:07,335
Or you can stay.

1537
02:06:14,235 --> 02:06:16,442
Maybe in the next life?

1538
02:06:18,740 --> 02:06:21,379
If we meet again
in the next life,

1539
02:06:21,509 --> 02:06:26,356
you will be my sworn enemy,
and I will show you no mercy.

1540
02:06:31,652 --> 02:06:33,098
<font color="#D900D9">(SOFT CHUCKLE)</font>

1541
02:06:41,362 --> 02:06:42,967
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHING)</font>

1542
02:08:43,617 --> 02:08:48,089
<font color="#D900D9">(OVERLAPPING CHATTER)</font>

1543
02:08:57,831 --> 02:09:00,277
<font color="#D900D9">(MOUTHING)</font>

1544
02:09:20,522 --> 02:09:23,401
Do you think you could just
look into my eyes and not blink,

1545
02:09:23,525 --> 02:09:26,665
and I'm gonna ask you some
questions that'll help you?

1546
02:09:26,794 --> 02:09:28,568
Maybe.

1547
02:09:28,696 --> 02:09:32,508
All right. Starting now.
You can't blink.

1548
02:09:32,634 --> 02:09:33,839
You just look in my eyes.

1549
02:09:33,968 --> 02:09:35,709
- You're already blinking.
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>

1550
02:09:35,837 --> 02:09:38,077
Starting now, all right?
What's your name?

1551
02:09:38,205 --> 02:09:41,312
- I told you...
- No, just say your name.

1552
02:09:41,442 --> 02:09:43,250
You don't remember?

1553
02:09:43,378 --> 02:09:47,223
- Just say your name.
- You're drunk.

1554
02:09:47,348 --> 02:09:49,191
You have to say your name.
And you blinked,

1555
02:09:49,317 --> 02:09:52,230
infringement, back to the start.
Now, say your name.

1556
02:09:52,353 --> 02:09:53,991
Winn.

1557
02:09:54,121 --> 02:09:59,538
- Now say your full name.
- Winn Manchester.

1558
02:09:59,661 --> 02:10:03,700
- Say it again.
- Winn Manchester.

1559
02:10:03,830 --> 02:10:07,107
- Say it again.
- Winn Manchester.

1560
02:10:07,235 --> 02:10:10,739
- Now, say it again.
- Winn Manchester.

1561
02:10:10,871 --> 02:10:13,375
Have you ever lived before?

1562
02:10:15,076 --> 02:10:16,884
I don't know.

1563
02:10:19,714 --> 02:10:22,160
Maybe this isn't your only life.

1564
02:10:25,219 --> 02:10:28,757
- I hope it isn't.
<font color="#D900D9">(FREDDIE LAUGHS)</font>

1565
02:10:31,593 --> 02:10:33,402
You're the bravest girl
I've ever known.

1566
02:10:33,527 --> 02:10:35,405
<font color="#D900D9">(BOTH LAUGHING)</font>

1567
02:10:38,232 --> 02:10:40,508
Now stick it back in,
it fell out.

